analysisPopulations.name: Screened Set
analysisPopulations.description: The Screened Set will include all participants who signed an informed consent form (ICF).

analysisPopulations.name: Enrolled Set
analysisPopulations.description: The Enrolled Set will include all participants who were enrolled in the study.

analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.label: FA
analysisPopulations.description: The Full Analysis (FA) Set will include all participants who were enrolled and received at least 1 dose of study drug. This set will be used for all efficacy analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Enrolled and received at least 1 dose of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Per Protocol Set
analysisPopulations.label: PP
analysisPopulations.description: The Per Protocol (PP) Set will be a subset of the FA Set who are compliant with the protocol and do not have any major protocol deviations that would impact the interpretability of the efficacy data. The PP Set will be used for sensitivity analyses of the primary efficacy endpoint.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Subset of the FA Set, compliant with the protocol, and without major protocol deviations impacting efficacy data

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Set
analysisPopulations.description: The Safety Set will include all participants who received at least 1 dose of study drug. This set will be used for all safety analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received at least 1 dose of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacokinetic Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.label: PK
analysisPopulations.description: The Pharmacokinetic (PK) Analysis Set will include all participants in the Safety Set who have sufficient plasma concentration data to allow for the derivation of at least 1 PK parameter. This set will be used for all PK analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Participant in the Safety Set with sufficient plasma concentration data for derivation of at least 1 PK parameter

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacodynamic Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.label: PD
analysisPopulations.description: The Pharmacodynamic (PD) Analysis Set will include all participants in the Safety Set who have sufficient PD data to allow for the derivation of at least 1 PD parameter. This set will be used for all PD analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Participant in the Safety Set with sufficient PD data for derivation of at least 1 PD parameter

characteristics.name: Age
characteristics.description: Age of participant, summarized as a continuous and categorical variable.

characteristics.name: Age at diagnosis of Wilson Disease (WD)
characteristics.description: Age at diagnosis of Wilson Disease.

characteristics.name: Medical/Surgical History
characteristics.description: Medical and surgical history coded using MedDRA.

characteristics.name: Prior medications for Wilson Disease (WD)
characteristics.description: Prior medications used to treat Wilson Disease.
